{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:02.239947+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6bbaad018f2e51fa8dae22ef0c3e9ee064041703)", "id": "lc_55e22886-27a0-428a-8251-c5cc401f174c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "server {\n    gzip on;\n    listen       80;\n    listen  [::]:80;\n    server_name  localhost;\n\n    location / {\n    root /usr/share/nginx/html;\n    index  index.html index.htm;\n    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;\n    }\n\n    location /admin {\n        alias /usr/share/nginx/html/admin;\n        index index.html index.htm;\n        try_files $uri $uri/ /admin/index.html;\n    }\n\n    location @rewrites {\n        rewrite ^(.*)$ /index.html last;\n    }\n}", "id": "lc_7f8a1f53-877c-48a5-b0ae-6b82cdf665fc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d3fcd416-e9d5-4fae-a11d-01af9d8c078e", "tool_call_id": "call_848163b6a8a94fafa28e8c93", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:02.247892+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 7b95ddcea190f56a111498024124db5de7d4e110)", "id": "lc_c996713c-68d0-4203-8b2c-3e16784465ed"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# https://taskfile.dev\n\nversion: '3'\n\ntasks:\n  default:\n    cmds:\n      - echo {{.CLI_ARGS}}\n    silent: true\n  \n  init:\n    cmds:\n      -  npm install -g conventional-changelog-cli\n      -  npm install -g standard-version\n      -  npm install -g commitizen\n      -  cp envs/.env.local .env\n      -  yarn install\n\n  changelog:\n    cmds:\n      - conventional-changelog -p angular -i CHANGELOG.md -s -r 0\n\n  release:\n    cmds:\n      - git fetch\n      - yarn release\n      - task changelog\n      - git add .\n      - git cz\n\n  commit:\n      cmds:\n          - git add .\n          - git cz\n          - git push\n\n", "id": "lc_58abaa29-5edd-4bd3-84b5-5a398eb005cd"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0e44a2c4-3b0e-4ab2-a794-500a6d29362e", "tool_call_id": "call_0cf1b8ada0704c4eb1d12172", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:02.255327+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 5a8caa55408a178b1c8935ed75bd16e03671b5d9)", "id": "lc_cd8b4632-d6ce-4616-89cd-e22d4f0bd58e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "NODE_ENV = prod\nVITE_BUILD_ENV = production\nVITE_HOST = lantron.ltd\nVITE_PORT = \nVITE_BASE_URL = ./\nVITE_OUTPUT_DIR = dist\nVITE_APP_BASE_API = https://mock.lantron.ltd", "id": "lc_defaf84e-fe4d-4e25-8f66-e6042a0bc751"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e34fb03b-2128-4bdd-91c7-1e9cbaaa5bdd", "tool_call_id": "call_2760a0e083b445adaaa0c607", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:18.176882+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a complete summary of how to run, build, and preview this React admin app locally and for different environments.\n\n---\n\n## How to Run Locally (Development)\n\n### 1. Install dependencies\n\nThe project uses **Yarn** as its package manager. First, copy the local environment file and install:\n\n```bash\ncp envs/.env.local .env\nyarn install\n```\n\nOr use the provided [Task](https://taskfile.dev) shortcut:\n\n```bash\ntask init\n```\n\n### 2. Start the dev server\n\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n\nThis runs `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host`, which loads `envs/.env.local` (via `vite.config.ts`). The app will be served at **`http://localhost:10086`** (as configured in `.env.local` with `VITE_PORT = 10086`). API requests are proxied to `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd`.\n\n### 3. Start the staging-flavoured dev server\n\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n```\n\nThis loads `envs/.env.stg` instead, pointing the API base URL at `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd`.\n\n---\n\n## How to Build for Production\n\nThere are three build scripts targeting different environments:\n\n| Script | Vite `--mode` flag | Env file loaded | API base URL |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `prod` | `envs/.env.prod` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `test` | `envs/.env.stg` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `production` | `envs/.env.prod` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\n> **Note:** `vite.config.ts` resolves the `.env` file by checking for a root `.env` first; if absent, it falls back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`. The `--mode` flag sets Vite's mode, while `cross-env NODE_ENV=...` sets the environment name used for the file lookup.\n\nAll builds output to the **`dist/`** directory.\n\n---\n\n## How to Preview a Build Locally\n\nAfter building, preview the production output with:\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\n\nThis runs `vite preview --host` and serves the contents of `dist/` on the port configured in your `.env`.\n\n---\n\n## Deployment Options\n\n### Docker (Nginx)\n\nThe `Dockerfile` performs a multi-stage build:\n\n1. **Builder stage** — installs dependencies and runs `yarn build`.\n2. **Nginx stage** — copies `dist/` into the Nginx image along with `nginx.conf`, which enables gzip, SPA fallback (`try_files … /index.html`), and listens on **port 80**.\n\nBuild and run:\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-admin\n```\n\n### GitHub Pages\n\n```bash\nyarn deploy\n```\n\nThis runs `gh-pages -d dist`, publishing the build output to GitHub Pages. The project's homepage is set to `https://reactZone.github.io/vite-react-ts-admin`.\n\n### Netlify\n\nA `netlify.toml` is included with a catch-all redirect rule (`/* → /index.html`, status 200) to support client-side routing.\n\n---\n\n### Quick-Reference Commands\n\n| Task | Command |\n|---|---|\n| First-time setup | `cp envs/.env.local .env && yarn install` (or `task init`) |\n| Local dev server | `yarn dev` (port 10086) |\n| Local dev (staging API) | `yarn dev:stg` |\n| Build for production | `yarn build` or `yarn build:prod` |\n| Build for staging | `yarn build:stg` |\n| Preview a build | `yarn serve` |\n| Deploy to GitHub Pages | `yarn deploy` |\n| Lint | `yarn lint` |\n| Lint & auto-fix | `yarn fix` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 935, "prompt_tokens": 8525, "total_tokens": 9460, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 14, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7296, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0013743306, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0005608806, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00081345}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863242-Mamx2psbCWvTviHs08uE", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-900f-72c2-9412-c0f23a951237-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8525, "output_tokens": 935, "total_tokens": 9460, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7296}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 14}}}}]}}}
